{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_65ab4959d9644e2c90bb01b8","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task: Port TTCPortalUser Class\n2\t\n3\t## Goal\n4\tCreate a TypeScript class that loads/saves per-user JSON data from GCS, matching the Python `TTCPortalUser` class exactly.\n5\t\n6\t## Context\n7\tThe legacy Python app stores all user data (form submissions, profile, config) as a single JSON file per user in GCS at `user_data/{email}.json`. The `TTCPortalUser` class is the data model — constructor loads from GCS, methods read/write form data, `saveUserData()` writes back. Every route that touches user data uses this class. The TS app currently has no persistence — this class enables it.\n8\t\n9\t## Read These Files First\n10\t1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/ttc_portal_user.py` (full file, ~477 lines) — the Python class to port. Focus on:\n11\t   - `__init__` and `initialize_user` (lines 356-371, 340-354) — constructor pattern\n12\t   - `load_user_data` / `save_user_data` (lines 309-338) — GCS read/write\n13\t   - `set_form_data` (lines 36-88) — form persistence with completeness check\n14\t   - `get_form_data` / `get_form_instances` (lines 212-232) — data retrieval\n15\t   - `is_form_submitted` / `is_form_complete` (lines 234-256) — boolean checks\n16\t   - `set_config` / `get_config` (lines 296-302) — user preferences\n17\t   - `set_home_country` / `get_home_country` (lines 289-294)\n18\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — the GCS utility (created in Task 1.1). Use `readJson()` and `writeJson()` for persistence.\n19\t3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` (lines 1-10) — import style reference\n20\t\n21\t## Changes Required\n22\t\n23\t**Create `app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts`:**\n24\t\n25\tPort the following from `ttc_portal_user.py`:\n26\t\n27\t| Python method | TS method | Notes |\n28\t|---|---|---|\n29\t| `__init__(self, user_email)` | `static async create(email: string)` | Async factory — can't do async in constructor. Calls `loadUserData`. |\n30\t| `initialize_user(self, data)` | `private initializeUser(data)` | Sets all fields from loaded JSON |\n31\t| `load_user_data(self, user_email)` | `private async loadUserData(email)` | Uses `readJson(GCS_PATHS.USER_CONFIG_PREFIX + email + '.json')` |\n32\t| `save_user_data(self)` | `async saveUserData()` | Uses `writeJson(path, this.toJSON())` — do NOT call `JSON.stringify()` here, `writeJson()` already handles serialization |\n33\t| `set_form_data(self, f_type, f_instance, ...)` | `setFormData(formType, formInstance, data, pageData, display)` | Port completeness check, `is_form_submitted`, `is_form_complete` flags, `last_update_datetime` |\n34\t| `get_form_data(self, f_type, f_instance)` | `getFormData(formType, formInstance)` | Returns stored answers dict |\n35\t| `get_form_instances(self, f_type)` | `getFormInstances(formType)` | Returns instance list with page_data and display |\n36\t| `is_form_submitted(self, f_type, f_instance)` | `isFormSubmitted(formType, formInstance)` | Boolean check |\n37\t| `is_form_complete(self, f_type, f_instance)` | `isFormComplete(formType, formInstance)` | Boolean check |\n38\t| `set_config` / `get_config` | `setConfig(params)` / `getConfig()` | User preferences |\n39\t| `set_home_country` / `get_home_country` | `setHomeCountry(country)` / `getHomeCountry()` | |\n40\t| `get_email` | `getEmail()` | |\n41\t\n42\t**Key implementation details:**\n43\t- `setFormData` must check completeness: iterate all fields, if any is null/empty string → `is_form_complete = false` (Python lines 53-56)\n44\t- `setFormData` must set `is_agreement_accepted`, `is_form_submitted`, `send_confirmation_to_candidate` from `i_agreement_accepted`, `i_form_submitted`, `i_send_confirmation_to_candidate` in form_data (Python lines 58-60). Use a `str2bool` helper: truthy strings → true.\n45\t- `setFormData` must store `default` copy when instance != 'default' (Python line 82-83)\n46\t- `setFormData` must set `last_update_datetime` to current UTC time as `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS` (Python line 75)\n47\t- **SKIP** `send_submission_emails` — email is deferred to Phase 6\n48\t- **SKIP** `get_public_photo_url` / `set_photo_file` — photo handling deferred\n49\t\n50\t**Export:** `TTCPortalUser` class + `GCS_PATHS` re-export from gcs.ts for convenience.\n51\t\n52\t## Constraints\n53\t- Do NOT add email sending logic\n54\t- Do NOT add photo URL logic (App Engine Images API not available)\n55\t- Do NOT modify any existing files\n56\t- Use `Date` for datetime, format to `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS` string when saving (matching Python `strftime`)\n57\t- Handle GCS NotFoundError gracefully in `loadUserData` — initialize with empty data (matching Python lines 317-319)\n58\t\n59\t## Verification\n60\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n61\t\n62\t## Completion\n63\t- Commit with message: `feat: port TTCPortalUser class for GCS-backed user persistence`\n64\t- Report: files changed, verification result\n65\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c47860c9-886d-45a4-8588-6f96430eddc4","uuid":"1f38a6c8-bd5a-4c82-be0a-9b9c0253f0f0","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:25:46.556Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/task-2.1-ttc-portal-user.md","content":"# Task: Port TTCPortalUser Class\n\n## Goal\nCreate a TypeScript class that loads/saves per-user JSON data from GCS, matching the Python `TTCPortalUser` class exactly.\n\n## Context\nThe legacy Python app stores all user data (form submissions, profile, config) as a single JSON file per user in GCS at `user_data/{email}.json`. The `TTCPortalUser` class is the data model — constructor loads from GCS, methods read/write form data, `saveUserData()` writes back. Every route that touches user data uses this class. The TS app currently has no persistence — this class enables it.\n\n## Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/ttc_portal_user.py` (full file, ~477 lines) — the Python class to port. Focus on:\n   - `__init__` and `initialize_user` (lines 356-371, 340-354) — constructor pattern\n   - `load_user_data` / `save_user_data` (lines 309-338) — GCS read/write\n   - `set_form_data` (lines 36-88) — form persistence with completeness check\n   - `get_form_data` / `get_form_instances` (lines 212-232) — data retrieval\n   - `is_form_submitted` / `is_form_complete` (lines 234-256) — boolean checks\n   - `set_config` / `get_config` (lines 296-302) — user preferences\n   - `set_home_country` / `get_home_country` (lines 289-294)\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — the GCS utility (created in Task 1.1). Use `readJson()` and `writeJson()` for persistence.\n3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` (lines 1-10) — import style reference\n\n## Changes Required\n\n**Create `app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts`:**\n\nPort the following from `ttc_portal_user.py`:\n\n| Python method | TS method | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `__init__(self, user_email)` | `static async create(email: string)` | Async factory — can't do async in constructor. Calls `loadUserData`. |\n| `initialize_user(self, data)` | `private initializeUser(data)` | Sets all fields from loaded JSON |\n| `load_user_data(self, user_email)` | `private async loadUserData(email)` | Uses `readJson(GCS_PATHS.USER_CONFIG_PREFIX + email + '.json')` |\n| `save_user_data(self)` | `async saveUserData()` | Uses `writeJson(path, this.toJSON())` — do NOT call `JSON.stringify()` here, `writeJson()` already handles serialization |\n| `set_form_data(self, f_type, f_instance, ...)` | `setFormData(formType, formInstance, data, pageData, display)` | Port completeness check, `is_form_submitted`, `is_form_complete` flags, `last_update_datetime` |\n| `get_form_data(self, f_type, f_instance)` | `getFormData(formType, formInstance)` | Returns stored answers dict |\n| `get_form_instances(self, f_type)` | `getFormInstances(formType)` | Returns instance list with page_data and display |\n| `is_form_submitted(self, f_type, f_instance)` | `isFormSubmitted(formType, formInstance)` | Boolean check |\n| `is_form_complete(self, f_type, f_instance)` | `isFormComplete(formType, formInstance)` | Boolean check |\n| `set_config` / `get_config` | `setConfig(params)` / `getConfig()` | User preferences |\n| `set_home_country` / `get_home_country` | `setHomeCountry(country)` / `getHomeCountry()` | |\n| `get_email` | `getEmail()` | |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- `setFormData` must check completeness: iterate all fields, if any is null/empty string → `is_form_complete = false` (Python lines 53-56)\n- `setFormData` must set `is_agreement_accepted`, `is_form_submitted`, `send_confirmation_to_candidate` from `i_agreement_accepted`, `i_form_submitted`, `i_send_confirmation_to_candidate` in form_data (Python lines 58-60). Use a `str2bool` helper: truthy strings → true.\n- `setFormData` must store `default` copy when instance != 'default' (Python line 82-83)\n- `setFormData` must set `last_update_datetime` to current UTC time as `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS` (Python line 75)\n- **SKIP** `send_submission_emails` — email is deferred to Phase 6\n- **SKIP** `get_public_photo_url` / `set_photo_file` — photo handling deferred\n\n**Export:** `TTCPortalUser` class + `GCS_PATHS` re-export from gcs.ts for convenience.\n\n## Constraints\n- Do NOT add email sending logic\n- Do NOT add photo URL logic (App Engine Images API not available)\n- Do NOT modify any existing files\n- Use `Date` for datetime, format to `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS` string when saving (matching Python `strftime`)\n- Handle GCS NotFoundError gracefully in `loadUserData` — initialize with empty data (matching Python lines 317-319)\n\n## Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n\n## Completion\n- Commit with message: `feat: port TTCPortalUser class for GCS-backed user persistence`\n- Report: files changed, verification result\n","numLines":65,"startLine":1,"totalLines":65}}}
